The '''Asom Bharatiya Janata Party''' is a break-away group of the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] in [[Assam]]. ABJP was founded by senior BJP leader and former [[Deputy inspector general of police|Deputy Inspector General of Police]], [[Hiranya Bhattacharya]] in 2001.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/2001/05/15/stories/15152035.htm|title=The Hindu : Double blow for BJP in Assam|website=www.thehindu.com|access-date=2017-01-30}}</ref> Bhattacharya had objected to the decision of BJP to align with the [[Asom Gana Parishad]].

Asom BJP contested the [[Assam Legislative Assembly election, 2001|2001 state assembly polls]] unsuccessfully.

