[[File:Båstads riots 1968.jpg|thumb|Police action in connection with the 1968 Båstad riots.]]

{{Expand Swedish|topic=sport|Båstadskravallerna |date=March 2009}}

The '''Båstad riots''' ({{lang-sv|Båstadskravallerna}}) is the name given to the riots that took place during a [[Davis Cup]] tennis match between [[Sweden]] and [[Rhodesia]] on May 3, 1968 in [[Båstad]], Sweden. 

Demonstrators were protesting the participation of the two [[apartheid]] countries, Rhodesia and [[South Africa]], in the international tennis competition. The countries were barred from other international sporting events. It became the most violent confrontation between the [[Swedish Police Authority|Swedish police]] and demonstrators during the 1960s. It was followed by a dialogue between the [[Government of Sweden|Swedish government]] and the demonstrators to curb the escalation of violence. The match later was played in secrecy, and Sweden won 4-1.<ref>{{cite news |last=Wijk |first=Johnny |url=http://www.dn.se/nyheter/sverige/idrotten-tjanar-pa-de-politiska-aktionerna |title=Idrotten tjänar på de politiska aktionerna |newspaper=[[Dagens Nyheter]] |date=2009-03-07 |access-date=2012-06-26 |language=Swedish}}</ref> 

