{{Infobox film | name = Gun Nation | image = | caption = | director = Zed Nelson | producer = Zed Nelson | writer = | starring = | narrator = | music = | cinematography = | editing = Noah Payne Frank | studio = | distributor = | released = {{film date|2016|09|16}} | runtime = 30 minutes | country = United Kingdom | language = | budget = | gross = }} '''''Gun Nation''''' is a 2016 [[documentary film]] directed and produced by British photographer and filmmaker Zed Nelson. The film explores issues surrounding [[gun ownership]], [[gun violence]], and [[gun culture in the United States]] and marks 18 years since the director's award-winning photography book of the same name.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.monstersandcritics.com/smallscreen/watch-gun-nation-documentary-asks-why-americas-love-affair-with-guns-persists/|title=Watch: Gun Nation documentary asks why America's love affair with guns persists|last=Wray|first=James|date=2016-09-16|website=Monsters and Critics|publisher=|language=en-US|access-date=2016-09-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://time.com/3790906/gun-nation-revisited-zed-nelsons-photographs-of-american-gun-culture/|title=Gun Nation Revisited: Zed Nelson's Photographs of American Gun Culture|last=Nelson|first=Zed|date=17 August 2012|website=TIME|publisher=|access-date=2016-09-17}}</ref> It was commissioned by ''[[The Guardian]]'' and by the Bertha Foundation, executive produced by [[en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charlie Phillips (documentary films)|Charlie Phillips]] and released online on September 16, 2016.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/ng-interactive/2016/sep/16/gun-nation-a-journey-to-the-heart-of-americas-gun-culture-video|title=Gun nation: a journey to the heart of America's gun culture – video|last=Nelson|first=Zed|date=2016-09-16|last2=Phillips|first2=Charlie|newspaper=The Guardian|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|last3=Payne-Frank|first3=Noah|last4=Nelson|first4=Zed|last5=Phillips|first5=Charlie|last6=Payne-Frank|first6=Noah|access