== Production == The development of the movie was revealed in the 19th light novel volume released in March 2016.<ref name="Movie Announced">{{cite web| url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-03-09/irregular-at-magic-high-school-light-novels-get-film/.99573| title=''Irregular at Magic High School'' Light Novels Get Film| publisher=[[Anime News Network]]| date=March 9, 2016| accessdate=March 9, 2016}}</ref> The film will feature a plot scripted by series creator Tsutomu Satō,<ref name="animefilm1">{{cite web| title=''Irregular at Magic High School The Movie''{{'}}s 1st Promo Video, Visual Revealed| url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-03-13/irregular-at-magic-high-school-the-movie-1st-promo-video-visual-revealed/.99738| publisher=Anime News Network| date=March 13, 2016| accessdate=March 13, 2016}}</ref> and will premiere in Japan on June 17, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-10-02/irregular-at-magic-high-school-movie-reveals-new-character-full-title-early-summer-2017-debut/.107145|title=Irregular at Magic High School Movie Reveals New Character, Full Title, Early Summer 2017 Debut|date=October 2, 2016|website=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=October 2, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-02-09/irregular-at-magic-high-school-film-reveals-june-17-opening-new-visual/.112034|title=Irregular at Magic High School Film Reveals June 17 Opening, New Visual|date=February 9, 2017|website=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=February 9, 2017}}</ref> All of the voice actors from the anime will reprise their roles.
At the Dengeki Game Festival 2017 event in Tokyo on Sunday March 12, more details were revealed about the film, including additional cast members, the theme song artist, and a fourth key visual. Also, the film's official website added the promotional video for the film. Risako Yoshida, who served as the unit director and a storyboarder on the anime television series, is directing the film at studio [[8-Bit (studio)|8-Bit]]. Original light novel series illustrator Kana Ishida is returning to serve as the character designer and chief animation director. Original light novel author Tsutomu Satō is writing an original new story for the film, and he and WriteWorks are writing the script. [[Taku Iwasaki]] is returning to compose the music.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-03-11/irregular-at-magic-high-school-anime-film-reveals-new-promo-video-more-cast-theme-song-artist-new-visual/.113311|title=Irregular at Magic High School Anime Film Reveals New Promo Video, More Cast, Theme Song Artist, New Visual|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=March 11, 2017|accessdate=March 11, 2017}}</ref> On April 19, the official website revealed three new cast members and a new visual,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-04-19/irregular-at-magic-high-school-anime-film-reveals-new-visual-additional-cast/.115019|title=Irregular at Magic High School Anime Film Reveals New Visual, Additional Cast|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 20, 2017|accessdate=April 20, 2017}}</ref> and on April 29, the third teaser was shown, including the date of a special screening.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-04-29/irregular-at-magic-high-school-anime-film-3rd-teaser-previews-garnidelia-song/.115482|title=Irregular at Magic High School Anime Film's 3rd Teaser Previews GARNiDELiA Song|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 30, 2017|accessdate=April 30, 2017}}</ref> On May 31, the official website began streaming a trailer for film. This included information about the original novel from Sato about Lina's past. It included the date of a special screening and the date fora meet and greet with the film's main personnel.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-05-31/irregular-at-magic-high-school-anime-film-trailer-streamed/.116828|title=Irregular at Magic High School Anime Film's Trailer Streamed|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=May 31, 2017|accessdate=June 7, 2017}}</ref> On June 13, [[Aniplex]] showed the first two minutes of the film<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-06-13/irregular-at-magic-high-school-anime-film-1st-2-minutes-posted/.117412|title=Irregular at magic high school Anime Film's 1st 2 Minutes Posted|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=June 13, 2017|accessdate=June 17, 2017}}</ref>
On June 10, 2017, [[Aniplex of America]] announced they had acquired the film for an English-language release, and announced that it would screen the film beginning on July 28, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-06-10/aniplex-usa-hosts-u.s-premiere-of-irregular-at-magic-high-school-anime-film-at-anime-expo-before-wider-release/.117290|title=Aniplex USA Hosts U.S. Premiere of Irregular at magic high school Anime Film at Anime Expo Before Wider Release|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=June 10, 2017|accessdate=June 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-06-11/irregular-at-magic-high-school-anime-film-english-subtitled-trailer-streamed/.117313|title=Irregular at magic high school Anime Film's English-Subtitled Trailer Streamed|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=June 11, 2017|accessdate=June 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-06-15/irregular-at-magic-high-school-anime-film-opens-in-u.s-on-july-28/.117494|title=Irregular at magic high school Anime Film Opens in U.S. on July 28|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=June 15, 2017|accessdate=June 17, 2017}}</ref> In Australia and New Zealand, [[Madman Entertainment]] announced at [[SMASH! (convention)|SMASH!]] 2017 that they had licensed the film for screening, and premiered the film on November 2, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.madman.com.au/news/special-madman-announcements-at-smash-2017/|title=Special Madman Announcements At SMASH 2017|last=Bortignon|first=Tegan|publisher=[[Madman Entertainment]]|date=August 20, 2017|accessdate=May 13, 2018}}</ref> The film was also screened in South East Asia by [[Odex]].
[[Aniplex]] released [[Blu-ray]] & [[DVD]] versions of the film in Japan on January 24, 2018.
The film's theme song is "Speed Star" by [[Garnidelia]].
==Reception== ===Box office=== On its opening weekend, the film debuted in 59 theaters across Japan and grossed a total of {{JPY|163 million}} from 107,000 admissions, opening at #5 at the Japanese box office.<ref name="GrossTotal"/>
